@full_implementation
title: Fully Implement the Law
on-arrival: reformer_approval += 3; moderate_approval += 1; hardliner_approval -= 4; popular_approval += 3; separatism += 2

We legalize religious organizations and remove state control over religious affairs. This is a historic step toward liberalization. However, nationalist and opposition groups across the various republics are emboldened as a key avenue through which they can exhibit their national identity is no longer stifled.

@implement_restricted
title: Implement a Restricted Version of the Law
on-arrival: reformer_approval += 1; moderate_approval += 3; hardliner_approval -= 2; popular_approval += 1; separatism += 1

We allow limited religious freedom but heavily monitor theological organizations. In practice, this means that the Communist Party retains control over appointments to positions of religious
authority and the sorts of political activism religious groups may engage in. This reassures moderates and hardliners while allowing for some social liberalization.

@delay_reform
title: Delay Religious Reform
on-arrival: reformer_approval -= 2; moderate_approval += 1; hardliner_approval += 3; popular_approval -= 1

Fearing political instability, we postpone religious freedom reforms, citing the need for further study and stability. This keeps the hardliners content, but not without protest from reformers and religious groups.

@reject_law
title: Reject the Law and Maintain State Atheism
on-arrival: reformer_approval -= 4; moderate_approval -= 2; hardliner_approval += 4; popular_approval -=3; separatism -=1

